## How to Use This Rule

**This rule applies automatically when selecting or integrating modules.**

**Agents should:**
1. **Verify required documentation** exists before using module
2. **Check documentation quality** against standards
3. **Test examples** to ensure they work
4. **Warn about gaps** if documentation is incomplete
5. **Help create documentation** if missing
6. **Follow documentation standards** when creating module docs

**Verification checklist:**
- [ ] README.md exists and is complete
- [ ] package.json exists with all dependencies
- [ ] INTEGRATION_GUIDE.md exists (if complex module)
- [ ] .env.example exists (if uses env vars)
- [ ] Migration files exist (if requires DB changes)
- [ ] Documentation is clear and accurate
- [ ] Examples are copy-pasteable and work
- [ ] Configuration is fully documented

**Quality checks:**
- [ ] Title and description are clear
- [ ] Dependencies are complete
- [ ] Installation steps work
- [ ] Usage examples are relevant
- [ ] API reference is complete
- [ ] Configuration is documented
- [ ] Troubleshooting is helpful

